        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 3:52PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 352 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wilmington Island, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Tybee Island, Wilmington Island, Fort Pulaski National Monument,
Montgomery, Wassaw Island, Skidaway Island, Isle Of Hope,
Whitemarsh Island, Wilmington and Wilmington Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
